metadata.title: Piper PA-28 Cherokee
aws::graph::propositions: # Piper PA-28 Cherokee Aircraft Variants
The PA-28-181 Archer III features a tapered wing compared to the PA-28-180 Archer.
The PA-28-181 Archer III is a four-place aircraft.
The PA-28-181 Archer III has fixed landing gear.
The PA-28-181 Archer III is classified as a landplane.
The PA-28-181 Archer III is powered by a Lycoming O-360-A4M engine.
The Lycoming O-360-A4M engine produces 180 hp (134 kW).
The PA-28-181 Archer III has a gross weight of 2,550 lb (1,157 kg).
The PA-28-181 Archer III was first certified on August 30, 1994.
The PA-28-181 Archer TX is a four-place aircraft.
The PA-28-181 Archer TX has fixed landing gear.
The PA-28-181 Archer TX is classified as a landplane.
The PA-28-181 Archer TX is powered by a Lycoming O-360-B4A engine.
The Lycoming O-360-B4A engine produces 180 hp (134 kW).
The PA-28-181 Archer TX has a maximum takeoff weight of 2,550 lb (1,157 kg).
The PA-28-181 Archer TX is produced as a trainer aircraft variant.
The PA-28-181 Archer TX features Garmin G1000 NXi avionics.
The PA-28-181 Archer LX is a four-place aircraft.
The PA-28-181 Archer LX has fixed landing gear.
The PA-28-181 Archer LX is classified as a landplane.
The PA-28-181 Archer LX is powered by a Lycoming O-360-B4A engine.
The Lycoming O-360-B4A engine produces 180 hp (134 kW).
The PA-28-181 Archer LX has a maximum takeoff weight of 2,550 lb (1,157 kg).
The PA-28-181 Archer LX is produced as a personal aircraft variant.
The PA-28-181 Archer LX features Garmin G1000 NXi avionics.
The PA-28-181 Archer DX is a four-place aircraft.
The PA-28-181 Archer DX has fixed landing gear.
The PA-28-181 Archer DX is classified as a landplane.
The PA-28-181 Archer DX is powered by a turbocharged Continental CD-155 diesel engine.
The turbocharged Continental CD-155 diesel engine produces 155 hp (116 kW).
The PA-28-181 Archer DX was introduced at AERO Friedrichshafen in April 2014.
The PA-28-181 Archer DLX is a four-place aircraft.
The PA-28-181 Archer DLX has fixed landing gear.
The PA-28-181 Archer DLX is classified as a landplane.
The PA-28-181 Archer DLX is powered by a turbocharged Continental CD-155 diesel engine.
The turbocharged Continental CD-155 diesel engine produces 155 hp (116 kW).
The PA-28-181 Archer DLX was introduced at AERO Friedrichshafen in April 2014.

text:
Changes from the PA-28-180 Archer include a tapered wing.
PA-28-181 Archer III
Four-place, fixed landing gear landplane, Lycoming O-360-A4M engine of 180 hp (134 kW), gross weight 2,550 lb (1,157 kg). First certified on August 30, 1994.

PA-28-181 Archer TX and LX
Four-place, fixed landing gear landplane, Lycoming O-360-B4A engine of 180 hp (134 kW), maximum takeoff weight 2,550 lb (1,157 kg).  Produced in Archer TX trainer and Archer LX personal aircraft variants, both with Garmin G1000 NXi avionics.

PA-28-181 Archer DX and DLX
Four-place, fixed landing gear landplane, turbocharged Continental CD-155 diesel engine of 155 hp (116 kW). Introduced at AERO Friedrichshafen in April 2014.
